TY  - JOUR
AU  - Broadie, Mark
AU  - Detemple, Jerome
T1  - American Option Valuation: New Bounds, Approximations, and a Comparison of Existing Methods
PY  - 1996
Y1  - 1996/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/9.4.1211
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 9
IS  - 4
SP  - 1211
EP  - 1250
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We develop lower and upper bounds on the prices of American call and put options written on a dividend-paying asset. We provide two option price approximations, one based on the lower bound (termed LBA) and one based on both bounds (termed LUBA). The LUBA approximation has an average accuracy comparable to a 1,000-step binomial tree with a computation speed comparable to a 50-step binomial tree. We introduce a modification of the binomial method (termed BBSR) that is very simple to implement and performs remarkably well. We also conduct a careful large-scale evaluation of many recent methods for computing American option prices.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/9.4.1211
ER  - 



